.SH NAME
HTMLCanvasElement.webglcontextcreationerror_event \- HTMLCanvasElement:
webglcontextcreationerror event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]webglcontextcreationerror\f[B]\f[R] event of the WebGL
API is fired if the user agent is unable to create a
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext\f[R] context.
.PP
This event has a \f[CR]WebGLContextEvent.statusMessage\f[R] property,
which can contain a platform dependent string with more information
about the failure.
.PP
This event does not bubble.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\[dq]webglcontextcreationerror\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {});

onwebglcontextcreationerror = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {};
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A \f[CR]WebGLContextEvent\f[R].
Inherits from \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EVENT PROPERTIES
\f[I]This interface inherits properties from its parent interface,
\f[CI]Event\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]WebGLContextEvent.statusMessage\f[R]
A read\-only property containing additional information about the event.
.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] canvas = document.getElementById(\[dq]canvas\[dq]);

canvas.addEventListener(
  \[dq]webglcontextcreationerror\[dq],
  (e) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    console.log(e.statusMessage || \[dq]Unknown error\[dq]);
  },
  \f[B]false\f[R],
);

